  "decision_conditions": [
    "The removal of the door contravenes the provisions of condition 4 of Listed Building Consent P100536 dated 18 June 2010.  The uncceptable loss of historic fabric and the unsatisfactory detail of the replacement door would have an adverse impact on the special architectural and historic interest of the listed building. The proposal is, therefore, considered to contravene the objectives policies HE7 and HE9 of PPS5 and policy 7.8 of the London Plan 2011 which seek to preserve and enhance the significance of heritage assets as well as the provisions of policy CS9 of Islington’s Core Strategy 2011 which seek to protect and enhance Islington’s built and historic environment."
